        <trans-unit id="102" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>FontDialog Component Overview (Windows Forms)</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="103" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The Windows Forms <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Forms.FontDialog&gt;</ph> component is a pre-configured dialog box, which is the standard Windows <bpt id="p1">**</bpt>Font<ept id="p1">**</ept> dialog box used to expose the fonts that are currently installed on the system.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="104" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Use it within your Windows-based application as a simple solution for font selection in lieu of configuring your own dialog box.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="105" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>By default, the dialog box shows list boxes for Font, Font style, and Size; check boxes for effects like Strikeout and Underline; a drop-down list for Script; and a sample of how the font will appear.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="106" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>(Script refers to different character scripts that are available for a given font, for example, Hebrew or Japanese.) To display the font dialog box, call the <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Forms.CommonDialog.ShowDialog%2A&gt;</ph> method.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="107" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Key Properties</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="108" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The component has a number of properties that configure its appearance.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="109" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The properties that set the dialog-box selections are <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Forms.FontDialog.Font%2A&gt;</ph> and <ph id="ph2">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Forms.FontDialog.Color%2A&gt;</ph>.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="110" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Forms.FontDialog.Font%2A&gt;</ph> property sets the font, style, size, script, and effects; for example, <ph id="ph2">`Arial, 10pt, style=Italic, Strikeout`</ph>.</source>
        </trans-unit>
